==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*διακονία / diakonia / dee-ak-on-ee'-ah

===Etymology===
*From [[διάκονος]] {{GG|1249}}; attendance (as a servant, etc.); figuratively (eleemosynary) aid, (official) service (especially of the Christian teacher, or technically of the diaconate): - 

===Noun===
'''διακονία'''

# (ad-) [[minister]] (-ing, -tration, -try), [[office]], [[relief]], [[service]] (-ing).

